  ---
  
  ## ðŸ“˜ Project Overview
  
  **RED EYES GitHub Bootcamp** is a scenario-based **desktop learning application** designed to teach **Git and GitHub workflows** the way they are actually used in professional software development environments.
  
  Rather than focusing on memorization of commands, this project emphasizes **decision-making**, **workflow safety**, and **real-world collaboration scenarios**. Learners are placed into situations they would encounter on real teams and are guided through best practices using immediate feedback and explanations.
  
  This project was **designed and built entirely by me**, from the curriculum and questions to the Python application and user interface.
  
  ---
  
  ## ðŸŽ¯ What This Project Is About
  
  This project exists to answer a simple question:
  
  > *How do developers really use Git and GitHub on teams?*
  
  The lab teaches:
  - When to branch (and why)
  - How pull requests protect production
  - How to handle merge conflicts safely
  - Why rebasing and force-pushing can be dangerous
  - How CI/CD fits into modern workflows
  - How teams collaborate without breaking each otherâ€™s work
  
  Every question represents a **real decision** a developer must make.
  
  ---
  
  ## ðŸ§  Learning Approach
  
  - 100 total questions
  - 4 structured learning modules
  - No repeated questions across modules
  - 50+ real-world scenario-based questions
  - Scenario-based explanations after incorrect answers
  - Final exam unlocked after completing all modules
  
  Mistakes are treated as **learning moments**, not failures.
  
  ---
  
  ## ðŸ“¦ Curriculum Modules
  
  | Module | Focus |
  |------|------|
  | Git Basics | Core version control concepts |
  | Branching & Merging | Real-world collaboration scenarios |
  | GitHub & Remotes | Pull requests, forks, issues |
  | Advanced Git Workflow | CI/CD, rebasing, stashing |
  
  Each module contains **25 unique questions**.
  
  ---
  
  ## ðŸ§ª Final Exam
  
  After completing all four modules, learners unlock a **Final Exam** that combines all 100 questions. This simulates a **bootcamp exit assessment** and reinforces long-term understanding.
  
  ---
  
  ## ðŸ–¥ï¸ Application Features
  
  - GitHub-inspired dark UI
  - 2Ã—2 module grid layout (no scrolling)
  - Module icons for clarity
  - Progress bar and live score tracking
  - Scenario-based explanation popups
  - macOS-safe window handling
  - Cross-platform (macOS, Windows, Linux)
  
